<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbc55975e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s3030c"><num value="3030c">§ 3030c.</num><heading> Audit; request for information</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idbc55975f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s3030c/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> The Assistant Secretary and the Comptroller General of the United States or any of their duly authorized representatives shall have access for the purpose of audit and examination to any books, documents, papers, and records that are pertinent to a grant or contract received under this subchapter.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idbc559760-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s3030c/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> State agencies and area agencies on aging shall not request information or data from providers which is not pertinent to services furnished pursuant to this chapter or a payment made for such services.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idbc559761-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/73/tIII/s313">Pub. L. 89–73, title III, § 313</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/95/478/tI/s103/b">Pub. L. 95–478, title I, § 103(b)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-18">Oct. 18, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1535">92 Stat. 1535</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/98/459/tIII/s311">Pub. L. 98–459, title III, § 311</ref>, <date date="1984-10-09">Oct. 9, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/1779">98 Stat. 1779</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/171/s3/a/13">Pub. L. 103–171, § 3(a)(13)</ref>, <date date="1993-12-02">Dec. 2, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/1990">107 Stat. 1990</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbc559762-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbc559763-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbc559764-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1993—Subsec. (a). <ref href="/us/pl/103/171">Pub. L. 103–171</ref> substituted “Assistant Secretary” for “Commissioner”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1984—<ref href="/us/pl/98/459">Pub. L. 98–459</ref> designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and added subsec. (b).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idbc559765-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
